Rating: 0
I made a few modifications to this recipe, mostly because the amount of sugar seemed excessive, and I was quite pleased with the end product. I substituted organic, unrefined sugar as it is naturally a bit sweeter and healthier than regular sugar. The following is a list of modifications made: topping: *reduced brown sugar to 1/2 cup *doubled cinnamon *added 1 1/2 tbsp butter to make streusel topping cake: *reduced sugar to 1 cup and used organic, unrefined *substituted 1 c. Greek yogurt for sour cream *added 1/2 c. sliced almonds preparation: *reduced oven temperature to 325 *used 2 small square cake pans instead of bundt pan *sprinkled topping on top of cake instead of swirling it throughout. The cake turned out beautifully; the streusel topping melted through the cake and the cake itself was tender and slightly chewy. It reminded me of the coffee cake my Grandmother used to make.

