I've been making this coffee cake for many years and it always gets rave reviews. For those of you who seem to be having trouble with the "look", may I recommend lining the tube pan with waxed paper? First grease the bottom of the pan and then put waxed paper, cut to size, on the bottom. It makes the cake come out of the pan easier and provides a slight "gloss" to the top. Easy and good. What more could a person ask for?

